caption.text: The unspoken rule: you can say all the right things, you can have the best ideas, you can have the most insane edits, but if your energy is off, your video will flop. Not enough creators focus on developing on camera presence. Even though it’s core to success. Do improv. Take an acting class. Do toastmasters. These things will help you much more than learning how to edit in a swoosh sound effect

caption.text:
A little bit naughty 🙊How did they get 2.6M followers in just 30 days?? 

Here are 3 things: 

1) They found a viral format and they stuck with it. Most creators abandon their best formats because they’re worried of becoming a broken record

2) They created a category of one. Soooo many cooking channels. None of them focus in on just cucumbers. This allows them to cut through the noise and attach their name to an entire category. Like popcorn and cinemas. You can shape consumer behaviour if you’re intentional 

3) The Innuendo - something said without explicitly being said. Leaving stuff to the imagination is 2+2=4 content. Most creators don’t have the confidence to do this, so they just tell you what to think (4=4 content)

Of course the main thing is they showed up with a big personality and did the work to carve out a niche. Do not underestimate this piece
